      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Situation at the time of occurrence",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Possible Causes",
            "header": true
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "hot day Stop the engine after driving and restart it about 3 hours later."
          },
          {
            "text": "If the purge control SOL.V. leaks when hot, evaporative gases in the fuel tank may enter the intake manifold, resulting in a thicker mixture and poor starting."
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "A windy day"
          },
          {
            "text": "If a headwind blows into the muffler, exhaust gases may be retained in the combustion chamber or intake manifold, resulting in non-starting or longer start-up times"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "cold day Refueled more than 2 months ago."
          },
          {
            "text": "If fuel is refueled during high temperatures (summer, etc.) and used during low temperatures (winter, etc.), starting performance may deteriorate and start-up time may increase."
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Use of undesignated fuels Use of alcohol fuels and gasoline additives"
          },
          {
            "text": "Use of unspecified fuel, alcohol fuel, or gasoline additives may increase engine start-up time"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Start cranking immediately after turning ignition ON mode Cranking is heavier than usual."
          },
          {
            "text": "If cranking is performed at the same time as the fuel pump is driven for 2 seconds after ignition ON mode, starting time may be longer due to voltage drop if the 12V battery is weak."
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Parking area is downhill or uphill Refueling warning light is on."
          },
          {
            "text": "When the fuel level is low in a parking lot other than on a flat road, the fuel pump may have difficulty drawing fuel, resulting in a lack of fuel pressure and a long start-up time."
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Modifying the vehicle. Check engine oil, ATF (CVTF), and A/C gas levels"
          },
          {
            "text": "Modifications to the ignition system, intake ducts, intake manifold, and muffler may increase startup time Use of engine oil or ATF other than specified, or high amounts of engine oil, ATF (CVTF), or A/C gas may increase engine resistance and start-up time"
          }
        ]
      ]
    }
